About The Company

Branded Media Corporation (BMCP) is a multimedia branding company that builds
brands and markets consumer products through a proprietary strategy, Branded Media.
As developed by the company, Branded Media is designed to increase sales of consumer
products by exposing brands and their messages through commercial and public television
programming, DVD, Video-on-Demand, direct response, home shopping television networks,
print, online and emerging media.

Reasons to buy this stock:

1)     BMCP management includes the former Senior VP of Martha Stewart Omnimedia,
        Emmy award-winning producers, as well as VH1 and NBC production executives. 
2)     BMCP is developing a brand of personal security products geared toward crisis
        management and notification during and immediately after a catastrophic event,
        e.g. terrorist attack. This model represents a strong opportunity within the
        booming Homeland Security industry.
3)     BMCP has attracted the attention of its newest director, Michael S. Scofield
        who oversees $110 billion in assets and investments.
4)     BMCP has acquired one of the largest film, music, and television libraries in
        the world which features such greats as Johnny Cash, Bette Davis, Duke Ellington,
        and Frank Sinatra.

